Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.

Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}, season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan over medium-high heat.

Add salmon (skin sides down); cook salmon until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Carrot Ragù ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat.

Add carrots, onion, and zucchini; season with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly browned, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{1%15oz can}, @water{1/4%cup}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> Use pan used for chicken or salmon here.

== Polenta ==

Meanwhile, heat a small #pot over medium heat.

Add @precooked polenta{1} and @water{1/3%cup}.

Mash with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp}; cook, whisking occasionally, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

> If polenta seems too thick, add water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches desired consistency.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1}.

== To Serve ==

Cut ciabatta on a diagonal into triangles and drizzle with @olive oil{}.

Divide polenta and ragù between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections.

Serve ciabatta on the side.

> Slice chicken crosswise (no need to slice salmon!). Serve chicken or salmon atop polenta.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.